*** Create Azure Blob Storage and Upload a Blob***

** Introduction **

Log in to the Azure portal.

Create a Storage Account
In the main menu search bar, type and select storage accounts.
Click + Create.
Set the following values:
Resource group: Existing resource group
Storage account name: unique name (Use Azure Resource Naming Conventions)
Region: (US) East US 2
Performance: Standard
Redundancy: locally-redundant storage (LRS)
Click Next: Advanced > Next: Networking > Next: Data protection.
Scroll down to Tracking and click Enable soft delete for blobs.
Click Next: Tags > Next: Review + create >
Once validation passes, click Create.
Note: Deployment may take several minutes.

** Create a Blob Container **
Once deployed, click *Go to resource.
On the left menu under Data storage, click Containers.
Click + Container.
In Name, enter "images".
Choose Blob (ananymous read access for blobs only).
Click Create.
Upload a Blob
Select the images container.
Click Upload.
Click the folder icon and select the file to upload from your local filesystem.
Click Open.
Click Upload.
Note: If the blob doesn't immediately appear, click Refresh.

Click the newly uploaded blob to open it.

In the Overview tab next to URL, click the copy icon and paste the blob URL in the address bar of a new browser tab.

An error message should display indicating that the blob data is private.

** Conclusion **
